Sure, you can add a preset to the schema which will provide a default setup for the section. Here's how you can modify the previous example to include a preset:

liquid
Copy code

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Hero section",
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Default",
      "category": "Custom"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}

{% stylesheet %}
.hero-section {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #f4f4f4;
}

.hero-image {
  width: 50%;
}

.hero-content {
  width: 50%;
}

.cta-button {
  display: inline-block;
  background-color: #ff0000;
  color: #ffffff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  text-decoration: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
}
{% endstylesheet %}